Where did you leave 'em?

29:28.599 --> 29:32.235
- Tell me where you left 'em!
- <i>Hey, Chris. Cool it.</i>

29:32.302 --> 29:34.637
Vic, he forgot the poles.
[ All Talking At Once ]

29:34.705 --> 29:37.140
<i>All right, all right,</i>
<i>all right. Alan, you left</i> <i>the poles behind?</i>

29:37.207 --> 29:41.844
- I know. It was stupid.
- Where'd you leave 'em? Do you remember?

29:41.912 --> 29:46.383
Sure.
Right by the bridge. On the other side.

29:46.450 --> 29:48.685
Well, you'll just have
to go back and get 'em.

29:50.120 --> 29:52.889
You mean now?
He's too scared.

29:52.956 --> 29:58.161
-Shut up.
-You'd better get going, Alan. It's only half a mile each way.

29:58.228 --> 30:03.967
